 src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_lightbulb.gif" align=absmiddle>  the perfect spiritual experiment</span><hr size=1> i still need to do some research to see if anyone else has tried my idea.  i just thought of a good way to prove or disprove the existence of a soul (at least for me)<br>
<br>
in doctrine and covenants the prophet joseph smith records the following [ D&amp;C 121:6-8 ] <br>
<br>
6 It is impossible for a man to be saved in ignorance.<br>
<br>
7 There is no such thing as immaterial matter. All spirit is matter, but it is more fine or pure, and can only be discerned by purer eyes;<br>
 <br>
8 We cannot see it; but when our bodies are purified we shall see that it is all matter.<br>
<br>
i think verse 6 is not only everyone will get the perfect knowledge one day but also counsil to understand all the science we can at the moment, even science that may 'fancy' to disprove my own faith.  i think most of us have a desire to eventually know it all anyway.<br>
<br>
so if this is the case i should be able to  weigh a bunch of mustard seed sprouts before and after grinding them up to see the change in mass.  i'm not exactly sure how many to use to see a measurable change but i can experiment.<br>
<br>
this should provide results that anyone may reproduce. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/breligiousdebate60574.showUserPublicProfile?gid=dag@religiousdebate60574>dag</A> at: 1/6/03 2:18:31 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#b9a1d0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/breligiousdebate60574.showUserPublicProfile?gid=mormongirl2>Mormongirl2</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Member</span><br>  Posts: 20<br> <font color=#3333ff>(1/6/03 2:20 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/freligiousdebate60574frm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=46.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_lightbulb.gif" align=absmiddle>  things that may ya say huh?</span><hr size=1> Ok Dag, you totally lost me. What did I miss here? - Shirene <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#9fb7df><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/breligiousdebate60574.showUserPublicProfile?gid=dag@religiousdebate60574>dag</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Member</span><br>  Posts: 92<br> <font color=#3333ff>(1/6/03 2:43 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/freligiousdebate60574frm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=46.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_lightbulb.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: things that may ya say huh?</span><hr size=1> i believe that plants have spirits the same way i believe everything else based on feelings.  if spirit is matter then it has mass and takes up space.  if i can confirm this fact (using plants instead of bugs because i want my blender to still be usable later on) then science can reproduce and accept the hypothesis until the results are explained better or jesus comes again.<br>
