<br>
Beware the false dichotomy as well.  Aside from assuming that grinding up a plant will remove the spirit, you have further assumed that there even is a spirit to remove, that it has a mass you can measure with the equipment on hand, that any change in mass is directly attributable to the exclusive loss of spirit and worst of all that if all the preceding works out, any spirit found is attributable to JC.<br>
<br>
Good luck.<br>
