<br>
The pull of of gravity on an object is 9.8 meters/sec 2 (That 2 is squared) If you were talking about a rock and a feather, yeah. The rock would hit first because the feather has more surface area (IE the surface to mass ratio is very different). If you would drop them in a vacuum, however, they would fall atthe same rate. This has already been proved by astronauts on the moon. <br>
